TITLE: Defining Task with Multiple Actions and File Iteration in Cake .NET Tool (C#)
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates an advanced composite task in the Cake .NET Tool, combining multiple chained actions and iterating over files. The task logs before and after actions, and processes files matching a glob pattern using DoesForEach. Requires Cake's Information and GetFiles functions. Inputs include the task name and file patterns. Outputs are console logs for actions and found files.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cake-build/website/blob/master/input/docs/writing-builds/tasks/defining-tasks.md#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
Task("A")
.Does(() => 
{
   Information("This action runs first.");
}).DoesForEach(GetFiles("./**/*"), f => 
{
   Information("Found file: "+f);
}).Does(() => {
   Information("This action runs last.");
});
```

