TITLE: Implementing Cake Frosting Tasks in C#
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows the implementation of three Cake Frosting tasks: HelloTask, WorldTask, and DefaultTask. It demonstrates task dependencies and asynchronous task execution.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cake-build/website/blob/master/input/docs/getting-started/setting-up-a-new-frosting-project.md#2025-04-23_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
[TaskName("Hello")]
public sealed class HelloTask : FrostingTask<BuildContext>
{
    public override void Run(BuildContext context)
    {
        context.Log.Information("Hello");
    }
}

[TaskName("World")]
[IsDependentOn(typeof(HelloTask))]
public sealed class WorldTask : AsyncFrostingTask<BuildContext>
{
    // Tasks can be asynchronous
    public override async Task RunAsync(BuildContext context)
    {
        if (context.Delay)
        {
            context.Log.Information("Waiting...");
            await Task.Delay(1500);
        }

        context.Log.Information("World");
    }
}

[TaskName("Default")]
[IsDependentOn(typeof(WorldTask))]
public class DefaultTask : FrostingTask
{
}
```

