TITLE: Defining Global Setup and Teardown Events in Cake .NET Tool (C#)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to register global setup and teardown hooks using the Cake .NET Tool runner. The Setup delegate is executed once before the first build task, while the Teardown delegate runs after the final task. These hooks allow initialization (such as starting services) and cleanup logic to be performed only if tasks are actually executed. Requires Cake scripting environment and a call to RunTarget to trigger these hooks.
SOURCE: https://github.com/cake-build/website/blob/master/input/docs/writing-builds/setup-and-teardown.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
Setup(context =>
{
    // Executed BEFORE the first task.
});

Teardown(context =>
{
    // Executed AFTER the last task.
});
```

