TITLE: Resolving and Executing Tool Path in Cake Task using C#
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates how to resolve the location of an executable (e.g., `nuget.exe`) using the `Resolve` method provided by `Context.Tools` (an instance of `IToolLocator`) within a Cake task. The resolved `FilePath` is then used with the `StartProcess` alias to execute the tool, passing arguments constructed using `ProcessArgumentBuilder`.
